Spanish Tortilla with Roasted Red Peppers and Peas
  --America's Test Kitchen

6 tbsp + 1 tsp evoo
1 1/2 lb yukon gold pottpes (3-4 medium) peeled, quartered lengthwise, and cut crosswise into 1/8" slices
1 small onion, halved and sliced thin
1 tsp salt, divided
1/4 tsp ground black pepper
8 large eggs
1/2 c jarred roasted red peppers, rinsed, dried, cut into 1/2" pieces
1/2 c frozen peas, thawed
garlic mayo (optional)

Toss 4 tbsp oil, potatoes, onion, 1/2 tsp salt, and pepper in large bowl until potato are thoroughly separated and coated. Heat 2 tbsp oil in 10" skillet over medium high heat until shimmering. Reduce heat to medium low, add potatoes, and set bowl aside without washing. Cover and cook, stirring with rubber spatula every 5 min, until potatoes ovver no resistance when poked with tip of paring knife, 22-28 min. It's ok if slices break into smaller pieces. Whisk eggs and remaining 1/2 tsp salt in reserved bowl until just combined. Using rybber spatula, fold hot potatoe mixture, red peppers, and peas into eggs until combined, making sure to scrape all potato mixture out of skillet. Return skillet to medium high heat, add remaining oil, and heat until just beginning to smoke. Add egg mixture and cook, skaing pan and colding mixture constantly for 15 s. Smooth top of mixture with spatula. Reduce heat to medium, cover, and cook, gently shaking pan every 30 s until bottom is golden brown and top is lightly set, ~2 min. Using spatula, loosen tortilla from pan, skaing back and forth until tortilla slide around freely in pan. Slide onto large plate, top with another plate, flip, and slide back into pan. Tuck edges into skillet. Return pan to medium heat and continur to cook, gently shaking pan every 30 s, until second side is golden brown, ~2 min longer. Cut into cubes or wedges and serve with garlic mayo (if desired).
